{
  "name": "Avelina Orieldt",
  "response": "Dr. Kellan claims self‑interest is the best guide to success, yet I fear it can ignite ambition while eclipsing the needs of my patrons and community. Prioritizing self‑interest risks alienating those I care about, because my ambition may eclipse generosity, and patrons might feel my art is driven by profit passion. I choose to temper ambition with community, ensuring my brush reflects both personal growth and the shared stories that give my work lasting everlasting meaning."
